  "text": "Electrophysiology. An EPC-7 patch clamp amplifier was used in wholeterminal and cell-attached patch recordings. An SR-830 lock-in amplifier (Stanford Research Systems) was connected to the patch-clamp amplifier to enable capacitance measurement [CITATION_1] . Signals were digitized with an ITC-16 interface connected to a Macintosh computer running Igor (WaveMetrics) and Pulse Control XOPs [CITATION_2] .",
